def clean(df):
    df = df.drop(["PassengerId", "Ticket", "Name"], axis=1)   # Dropping redundant columns
    
    cols = ["SibSp", "Parch", "Fare", "Age"]  # Filling continuous columns with median values
    for col in cols:
        df[col].fillna(df[col].median(), inplace=True)
        
    df.Embarked.fillna(df["Embarked"].mode()[0], inplace=True) # Filling the "Embarked" column with most frequent value

    df["Cabin"].fillna('U', inplace=True) # Filling the "Cabin" column with 'U' (Unknown)

    for i in range(len(df["Cabin"])):    # Keeping the first letter, which makes the column's values to be divided by zones
      df["Cabin"].replace(df["Cabin"][i], df["Cabin"][i][0], inplace=True)
    
    return df

data = clean(data)
test = clean(test)

def enc_oh(df, is_test=False):
    #One Hot Encoding
    DSex = pd.get_dummies(df['Sex'])
    DCabin = pd.get_dummies(df['Cabin'],prefix='Cabin')
    DEmbarked = pd.get_dummies(df['Embarked'],prefix='Embarked')

    if is_test:
      # These columns are missing in the test
      DCabin['Cabin_T'] = 0
      DCabin['Cabin_U'] = 0

    df = df.drop(['Sex', 'Cabin', 'Embarked'], axis=1)
    df = df.join([DSex, DCabin, DEmbarked])

    return df
  
data = enc_oh(data)
test = enc_oh(test, True)

def plot_learning_curve(estimator, title, X, y, ylim=None, cv=None,
                        n_jobs=-1, train_sizes=np.linspace(.1, 1.0, 5)):
    """Generate a simple plot of the test and training learning curve"""
    plt.figure()
    plt.title(title)
    if ylim is not None:
        plt.ylim(*ylim)
    plt.xlabel("Training examples")
    plt.ylabel("Score")
    train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(
        estimator, X, y, cv=cv, n_jobs=n_jobs, train_sizes=train_sizes)
    train_scores_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
    train_scores_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)
    test_scores_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
    test_scores_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)
    plt.grid()

    plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_scores_mean - train_scores_std,
                     train_scores_mean + train_scores_std, alpha=0.1,
                     color="r")
    plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_scores_mean - test_scores_std,
                     test_scores_mean + test_scores_std, alpha=0.1, color="g")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, train_scores_mean, 'o-', color="r",
             label="Training score")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, test_scores_mean, 'o-', color="g",
             label="Cross-validation score")

    plt.legend(loc="best")
    return plt

g = plot_learning_curve(gsadaDTC.best_estimator_,"AdaBoost learning curves",X,t,cv=kfold)
g = plot_learning_curve(gsGBC.best_estimator_,"GradientBoosting learning curves",X,t,cv=kfold)
g = plot_learning_curve(gsMLPC.best_estimator_,"MLP curves",X,t,cv=kfold)
g = plot_learning_curve(gsSGDC.best_estimator_,"SGD learning curves",X,t,cv=kfold)
g = plot_learning_curve(gsLDAC.best_estimator_,"LDA learning curves",X,t,cv=kfold)

precisions, recalls, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(t, y_pre)

def plot_precision_recall_vs_thresholds(precisions, recalls, thresholds):
    plt.figure(figsize = (8,8))
    plt.plot(thresholds, precisions[:-1], "b--", label="Precision")
    plt.plot(thresholds, recalls[:-1], "g--", label="Recall")
    plt.xlabel("Threshold")
    plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.15, 1), loc='upper left', borderaxespad=1)
    plt.grid(b=True, which="both", axis="both", color='gray', linestyle='-', linewidth=3)

plot_precision_recall_vs_thresholds(precisions, recalls, thresholds)
plt.show()
